ksprfs.ksprfs_engine_desc: More powerful version of the TRR-1.

Like their earlier 30 series, the 40 series of orbital maneuvering engines continues to outsell its closest competitor, the Thrustmax 50. The Omnimax 40T features digitally controlled thrust vectoring and nozzle pitch trim. The 40T is optimized for service in a vacuum as opposed to atmospheres.

Latest engine from the makers of the 200 series. The Thrustmax 300 features digitally controlled gimbling, electronic fuel injection, flame out recovery, and their patented 'Cyromax" nozzle cooling system.
Much more powerful than their 100 series, the Thrustmax 200 has a high thrust to weight ratio while in atmosphere but loses out to more efficient engines whilst in a vacuum.
Upscaled SRB for your really big rockets.
An orbital engine for low orbit applications. Saves on weight compared to the larger KW SPS since it doesn't need to be as powerful.
